cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep convolutional energy-based model for modeling volumetric shape patterns, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The model is trained using maximum likelihood and MCMC, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model can also be interpreted as a mode seeking and mode shifting process, which is a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
